bor. This regime not only molds inmates into compliant workers willing and expected to accept any ";bad"; job upon release, it also compels many Americans to work in such jobs under threat of incarceration, all the while bolstering their ";exploitability"; and socioeconomic marginality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEx-convictsxEmploymentzUnited States. 0aPrecarious employmentzUnited States. 0aPrisonersxEmploymentzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aBonds, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodman, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatton, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatton, Erin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHughett, Amanda Bell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParker, Caroline M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPurser, Gretchen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStevens, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZatz, Noah D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391520 cprintz978052030533540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052097